{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"831067cb-344c-4fda-93d3-84a9c508d0f5","content":"Here are the likely causes and fixes for each:\n\n**1. `GoToAsync(\"productdetails\")` throws an exception**\n\nThe route isn't registered. Pages not declared in Shell's XAML hierarchy must be explicitly registered:\n\n```csharp\n// In AppShell constructor or MauiProgram.cs\nRouting.RegisterRoute(\"productdetails\", typeof(ProductDetailsPage));\n```\n\n**2. `GoToAsync(\"//products/active\")` navigates but nothing visible changes**\n\nYour Shell XAML items likely lack explicit `Route` properties. Shell auto-generates routes from type names, so `//products/active` may silently resolve to the already-displayed item. Fix by setting `Route` explicitly at every level:\n\n```xml\n<FlyoutItem Route=\"products\">\n    <Tab Route=\"active\">\n        <ShellContent Route=\"list\" ContentTemplate=\"{DataTemplate local:ActiveProductsPage}\" />\n    </Tab>\n</FlyoutItem>\n```\n\nThen navigate with the full matching path: `//products/active/list`.\n\n**3. Slow startup with 12 pages**\n\nPages are being instantiated eagerly. Use `ContentTemplate` with a `DataTemplate` instead of inline page instances so pages are created only when first navigated to:\n\n```xml\n<!-- ❌ Eager — page created at Shell startup -->\n<ShellContent>\n    <local:MyPage />\n</ShellContent>\n\n<!-- ✅ Deferred — page created on first navigation -->\n<ShellContent ContentTemplate=\"{DataTemplate local:MyPage}\" />\n```\n\nThis defers construction of all 12 pages until they're actually visited.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"98c472df-1aea-4a64-aa5f-20bba11390f5","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about three common .NET MAUI Shell navigation issues. These are well-known problems with known solutions. Let me provide concise, accurate answers.\n\n1. `GoToAsync(\"productdetails\")` throws an exception - This is likely because the route isn't registered. In MAUI Shell, routes that aren't defined in the Shell visual hierarchy (XAML) must be registered with `Routing.RegisterRoute`.\n\n2. `GoToAsync(\"//products/active\")` navigates but nothing visible changes - This is likely because the ShellContent doesn't have a proper `ContentTemplate` or the page isn't being created/refreshed. Another common cause: the route resolves to a tab/page that's already \"selected\" visually, or the content is defined but not rendered. Most commonly, this happens when you have Shell items without `ContentTemplate` (using `DataTemplate`) so pages get created upfront and the visual state doesn't update. Actually, the most common cause is that the route matches but the `Shell.Current.CurrentItem` is already set to that item visually - or more likely, the ShellContent uses `Content` property directly instead of `ContentTemplate`, so the page exists but isn't displayed. Another very common cause: the `FlyoutItem`/`Tab`/`ShellContent` has `FlyoutItemIsVisible=\"False\"` and the Shell can't visually show it, OR the route structure doesn't match what you think. Let me reconsider - the most common cause of \"GoToAsync with absolute route works but nothing displays\" is usually a mismatch between the route definition and the Shell hierarchy structure. The most likely culprit is that you're navigating to a route that's already the currently displayed page—Shell resolves it correctly but doesn't re-render since nothing actually changed visually. This usually happens when `ShellContent` items don't have explicit `Route` properties set, so Shell auto-generates them from class names, causing `//products/active` to map to the wrong place in your hierarchy. me give a practical answer:\n\n**Problem 2 most likely cause:** The `Route` property isn't set on the Shell items in XAML, so the auto-generated routes don't match `//products/active`. Or the `ShellContent` for \"active\" is under a `Tab` whose route isn't \"products\". You need to explicitly set `Route=\"products\"` on the parent `FlyoutItem`/`Tab` and `Route=\"active\"` on the `ShellContent`.\n\nActually wait - if the route didn't match, it would throw an exception. If it navigates without exception but nothing changes... \n\nThe most common cause I've seen documented: **You're already on that page/tab.** Shell doesn't re-create or re-navigate when the destination is the current location. Or alternatively, the page's content isn't being set up in `OnNavigatedTo`/`OnAppearing` correctly.\n\nBut thinking about this more carefully, the real issue is probably that Shell items lack explicit routes, so it's either auto-generating mismatched paths or the implicit `ShellContent` shorthand is creating an unexpected route structure that doesn't align with `//products/active`.\n\nThe three core fixes are: register any pages not in the Shell hierarchy, set explicit `Route` properties on every Shell item to avoid auto-generation surprises, and use `ContentTemplate` with deferred instantiation instead of inline page declarations to avoid creating all 12 pages upfront.","outputTokens":1779,"requestId":"4842:B22B0:BE56CB:DD2102:69F3FDA4"},"id":"ba8ff7ad-74ca-4468-8803-932024f66b42","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:11:39.570Z","parentId":"29fc4941-dc7e-4021-900f-c6b4cc1240c5"}
